#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:2
msgid "fish - the friendly interactive shell"
msgstr "fish - 友善的互動式外殼"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:7
msgid ""
"fish [OPTIONS] [FILE [ARG ...]]\n"
"fish [OPTIONS] [-c COMMAND [ARG ...]]"
msgstr ""
"fish [OPTIONS] [FILE [ARG ...]]\n"
"fish [OPTIONS] [-c COMMAND [ARG ...]]"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:13
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:15
msgid ""
":command:`fish` is a command-line shell written mainly with interactive use "
"in mind. This page briefly describes the options for invoking :command:"
"`fish`. The :ref:`full manual <intro>` is available in HTML by using the :"
"command:`help` command from inside fish, and in the `fish-doc(1)` man page. "
"The :doc:`tutorial <../tutorial>` is available as HTML via ``help tutorial`` "
"or in `man fish-tutorial`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:21
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:23
msgid "**-c** or **--command=COMMAND**"
msgstr "**-c** 或 **--command=COMMAND**"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:24
msgid ""
"Evaluate the specified commands instead of reading from the commandline. Any "
"additional positional arguments are used as ``$argv``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:27
msgid "**-C** or **--init-command=COMMANDS**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:28
msgid ""
"Evaluate specified commands after reading the configuration but before "
"executing command specified by **-c** or reading interactive input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:30
msgid "**-d** or **--debug=DEBUG_CATEGORIES**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:31
msgid ""
"Enables debug output and specify a pattern for matching debug categories. "
"See :ref:`Debugging <debugging-fish>` below for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:34
msgid "**-o** or **--debug-output=DEBUG_FILE**"
msgstr "**-o** 或 **--debug-output=DEBUG_FILE**"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:35
msgid ""
"Specifies a file path to receive the debug output, including categories and :"
"envvar:`fish_trace`. The default is standard error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:38
msgid "**-i** or **--interactive**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:39
msgid "The shell is interactive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:41
msgid "**-l** or **--login**"
msgstr "**-l** 或 **--login**"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:42
msgid "Act as if invoked as a login shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:44
msgid "**-N** or **--no-config**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:45
msgid "Do not read configuration files."
msgstr "不要讀取組態檔。"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:47
msgid "**-n** or **--no-execute**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:48
msgid "Do not execute any commands, only perform syntax checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:50
msgid "**-p** or **--profile=PROFILE_FILE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:51
msgid ""
"when :command:`fish` exits, output timing information on all executed "
"commands to the specified file. This excludes time spent starting up and "
"reading the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:54
msgid "**--profile-startup=PROFILE_FILE**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:55
msgid "Will write timing for ``fish`` startup to specified file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:57
msgid "**-P** or **--private**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:58
msgid ""
"Enables :ref:`private mode <private-mode>`: **fish** will not access old or "
"store new history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:60
msgid "**--print-rusage-self**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:61
msgid "When :command:`fish` exits, output stats from getrusage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:63
msgid "**--print-debug-categories**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:64
msgid "Print all debug categories, and then exit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:66
msgid "**-v** or **--version**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:67
msgid "Print version and exit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:69
msgid "**-f** or **--features=FEATURES**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:70
msgid ""
"Enables one or more comma-separated :ref:`feature flags <featureflags>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:72
msgid ""
"The ``fish`` exit status is generally the :ref:`exit status of the last "
"foreground command <variables-status>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:77
msgid "Debugging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:79
msgid ""
"While fish provides extensive support for :ref:`debugging fish scripts "
"<debugging>`, it is also possible to debug and instrument its internals. "
"Debugging can be enabled by passing the **--debug** option. For example, the "
"following command turns on debugging for background IO thread events, in "
"addition to the default categories, i.e. *debug*, *error*, *warning*, and "
"*warning-path*: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:84
msgid "> fish --debug=iothread"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:86
msgid ""
"Available categories are listed by ``fish --print-debug-categories``. The "
"**--debug** option accepts a comma-separated list of categories, and "
"supports glob syntax. The following command turns on debugging for "
"*complete*, *history*, *history-file*, and *profile-history*, as well as the "
"default categories: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:90
msgid "> fish --debug='complete,*history*'"
msgstr "> fish --debug='complete,*history*'"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:92
msgid ""
"Debug messages output to stderr by default. Note that if :envvar:"
"`fish_trace` is set, execution tracing also outputs to stderr by default. "
"You can output to a file using the **--debug-output** option: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:95
msgid ""
"> fish --debug='complete,*history*' --debug-output=/tmp/fish.log --init-"
"command='set fish_trace on'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:97
msgid ""
"These options can also be changed via the :envvar:`FISH_DEBUG` and :envvar:"
"`FISH_DEBUG_OUTPUT` variables. The categories enabled via **--debug** are "
"*added* to the ones enabled by $FISH_DEBUG, so they can be disabled by "
"prefixing them with **-** (**reader-*,-ast*** enables reader debugging and "
"disables ast debugging)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:100
msgid ""
"The file given in **--debug-output** takes precedence over the file in :"
"envvar:`FISH_DEBUG_OUTPUT`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:103
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:105
msgid "To just start fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:107
msgid "fish"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:109
msgid "To run a file with fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:111
msgid "fish /path/to/script.fish"
msgstr "fish /path/to/script.fish"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:113
msgid "To run some commands with fish::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:115
msgid "fish -c 'echo Hi there!'"
msgstr "fish -c 'echo Hi there!'"

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:117
msgid "You can also pass arguments to those commands::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:119
msgid ""
"> fish -c 'printf %s\\n $argv' \"first line\" \"second line\"\n"
"first line\n"
"second line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:123
msgid "To run a script, except read this other file first::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:125
msgid "fish --init-cmd \"source otherfile\" script.fish"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:127
msgid ""
"To :ref:`profile <profiling>` fish's startup and find what takes the most "
"time in your configuration::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish.rst:129
msgid ""
"fish --profile-startup /tmp/start.prof -ic exit\n"
"sort -nk2 /tmp/start.prof"
msgstr ""
